lds largest oilfield services company schlumberger employs approximately  people representing more than  nationalities working in more than  countries schlumberger has four principal executive offices located in paris houston london and the hague schlumberger is incorporated in willemstad curaçao as schlumberger nv and trades on the new york stock exchange euronext paris the london stock exchange and six swiss exchange schlumberger is a fortune global  company ranked  in  and also listed in forbes global  ranked  in  contents  history  corporate affairs  france  united states  environmental record  radioactive sources  spills  brownfields  deepwater horizon  see also  references  external links historyedit this houston building as of  houses the schlumberger us executive offices schlumberger complex in sugar land texas schlumberger was founded in  by brothers conrad and marcel schlumberger from the alsace region in france as the société de prospection électrique french electric prospecting company the company recorded the firstever electrical resistivity well log in merkwillerpechelbronn france in  today schlumberger supplies the petroleum industry with services such as seismic acquisition and processing formation evaluation well testing and directional drilling well cementing and stimulation artificial lift well completions flow assurance and consulting and software and information management the company is also involved in the groundwater extraction and carbon capture and storage industries the brothers had experience conducting geophysical surveys in countries such as romania canada serbia south africa the democratic republic of the congo and the united states the new company sold electricalmeasurement mapping services and recorded the firstever electrical resistivity well log in merkwillerpechelbronn france in  the company quickly expanded logging its first well in the us in  in kern county california in  the schlumberger well surveying corporation was founded in houston later evolving into schlumberger well services and finally schlumberger wireline  testing schlumberger invested heavily in research inaugurating the schlumbergerdoll research center in ridgefield connecticut in  contributing to the development of a number of new logging tools in  schlumberger limited was incorporated as a holding company for all schlumberger businesses which by now included american testing and production company johnston testerscitation needed over the years schlumberger continued to expand its operations and acquisitions in  dowell schlumberger  schlumberger  dow chemical which specialized in pumping services for the oil industry was formed in  schlumberger limited became listed on the new york stock exchange that same year schlumberger purchased daystrom an electronic instruments manufacturer in south boston virginia which was making furniture by the time the division was sold to sperry  hutchinson in  schlumberger purchased  of forex in  and merged it with  of languedocienne to create the neptune drilling company the first computerized reservoir analysis saraband was introduced in  the remaining  of forex was acquired the following year neptune was renamed forex neptune drilling company in  fairchild camera and instrument including fairchild semiconductor became a subsidiary of schlumberger limited schlumberger established the first international data links with email in  in  schlumberger opened their cambridge research center in cambridge england and in  it was renamed the schlumberger gould research center after the companys former ceo andrew gould the sedco drilling rig company and half of dowell of north america were acquired in  resulting in the creation of the anadrill drilling segment a combination of dowell and the analysts drilling segments forex neptune was merged with sedco to create the sedco forex drilling company the following year when schlumberger purchased merlin and  of gecocitation needed in  schlumberger completed their purchases of neptune north america bosco and cori italy and allmess germany that same year national semiconductor acquired fairchild semiconductor from schlumberger for  million in  schlumberger acquired praklaseismos and pioneered the use of geosteering to plan the drill path in horizontal wellscitation needed schlumberger acquired software company geoquest systems in  with the purchase came the conversion of sinet to tcpip and www capability in the s schlumberger bought out the petroleum division aeg meter and eclipse reservoir study team intera technologies corp a joint venture between schlumberger and cable  wireless resulted with the creation of omnes which then handled all of schlumbergers internal it business oilphase and camco international were also purchasedcitation needed in  schlumberger and smith international created a joint venture mi llc the worlds largest drilling fluids or mud company the company consists of  smith international and  schlumberger since the joint venture was prohibited by a  antitrust consent decree barring smith from selling or combining their fluids business with certain other companies including schlumberger the us district court in washington dc found smith international inc and schlumberger ltd guilty of criminal contempt and fined each company  and placed each company on five years probation both companies also agreed to pay a total of  million representing a full disgorgement of all of the joint ventures profits during the time the companies were in contempt in  the gecoprakla division was merged with western geophysical to create the seismic contracting company westerngeco of which schlumberger held a  stake the remaining  belonging to competitor baker hughes sedco forex was spun off and merged with transocean drilling company in citation needed in  schlumberger acquired the it consultancy company sema plc for  billion the company was an athens  summer olympics partner but schlumbergers venture into it consultancy did not pay off and divestiture of sema to atos origin was completed that year for  billion the cards division was divested through an ipo to form axalto which later merged with gemplus to form gemalto and the messaging solutions unit was spun off and merged with taral networks to form airwide solutions in  the automated test equipment group part of the  fairchild semiconductor acquisition was spun off to nptest holding which later sold it to credencecitation needed in  schlumberger business consulting was launched based in paris it is the companys management consultancy arm  in  schlumberger purchased waterloo hydrogeologicunreliable source which was followed by several other groundwater industry related companies such as westbay instruments and van essen instruments also that year schlumberger relocated its us corporate offices from new york to houston in  schlumberger purchased the remaining  of westerngeco from baker hughes for us billion also that year the schlumbergerdoll research center was relocated to a newly built research facility in cambridge massachusetts to replace the ridgefield connecticut research center the facility joins the other research centers operated by the company in cambridge england moscow russia stavanger norway and dhahran saudi arabia in  the acquisition of smith international in an allstock deal valued at  billion was announced the sale price is ashare price was  percent higher than smith closing price on  february  the deal is the biggest acquisition in schlumberger history the merger was completed on august   also announced in  were schlumberger plans to acquire geoservices a frenchbased company specializing in energy services in a deal valued at  billion including debt in  schlumberger announced the purchase of the remaining shares of ses holdings limited “saxon” a calgarybased provider of international land drilling services from first reserve and certain members of saxon management the transaction is subject to customary closing conditions including the receipt of regulatory approvals schulmberger had a minority share in saxon previously in  schlumberger was indicted by the us department of justice for sanction violations of conducting business in iran and sudan the company was fined  million amounting to the largest fine for sanctions to date due to a downturn in the global oil  gas industry in  schlumberger announced  layoffs accounting for  of their total workforce in august  schlumberger agreed to acquire oilfield equipment manufacturer cameron international for  billion schlumberger is the global leader in hydraulic fracturing patents as of  corporate affairsedit franceedit its paris offices are in le palatin  in the la défense business district and in puteaux france near paris united statesedit schlumberger maintains a acre  ha campus at the northeast corner of us highway a and gillingham lane in sugar land texas as of  schlumberger is the second largest employer in the city in  schlumberger announced that it was moving its us corporate headquarters to the sugar land facility from its houston office building the company plans to build new buildings with a scheduled completion time of late  they include a total of  square feet  m of class a office space and an amenities building with  square feet  m of space in the s the north american headquarters were established in houston in the s the companys top executives in north america were relocated to new york city by  the head office had  executives and support staff by that year the company was moving that office to a building near the houston galleria schlumberger moved its houstonarea offices from  gulf freeway in houston to the sugar land campus in  environmental recordedit in  newsweek released their green rankings  a ranking of the  largest corporations on track records on a number of environmental issues schlumberger was ranked th out of  overall and rd out of  in their industry newsweek remarked that to mitigate global warming schlumberger has invested in carbon sequestration which involves longterm storage of co and that the companys seismic survey ships are  to  more fuelefficient than those of other seismic contractors from using fuels that emit less pollution and towing equipment that creates less drag on the vessels radioactive sourcesedit in  a radioactive canister imported by schlumberger was recovered in the western australian outback desert the canister had been lost in by the companys transport partner when the improperly secured container fell off the trailer on which it was being transported in  the aberdeen sheriff court fined schlumberger oilfield uk £ for losing a radioactive source on the rig floor on the ensco  mobile drilling rig in the north sea for  hours spillsedit in  the pennsylvania department of environmental protection fined chesapeake appalachia llc and schlumberger technology corp more than  each for a hydrochloric acid spill in february  at chesapeakes chancellor natural gas well site in asylum township bradford county pennsylvania officials said the leak did not contaminate groundwater brownfieldsedit in  as the current owner of a facility in pickens south carolina schlumberger agreed to pay  million to federal and state agencies for a problem caused by the previous owner sangamoweston a capacitor manufacturing plant the cause of the problem was from polychlorinated biphenyls pcb released into the environment by sangamoweston from  to  according to the justice departments environment and natural resources division an additional agreement by schlumberger to purchase and remove dams will directly improve the twelvemile creek south carolina ecosystem and provide significant environmental benefits for the affected communities deepwater horizonedit schlumberger was contracted to perform wireline logging on the deepwater horizon oil rig in the gulf of mexico in  however the wireline log was cancelled and the schlumberger standby crew was released by bp and left the rig earlier on the same day of the deepwater horizon explosion see alsoedit houston portal companies portal energy portal westerngeco list of oilfield service companies referencesedit  a b c d e schlumberger limited slb yahoo finance   wethe david january   schlumberger fourthquarter profit rises as drilling booms bloomberg news   schlumberger to cut  jobs on oilprice plunge reuters january   – via cnbc    schlumberger profile bloomberg businessweek check url value help retrieved april     schlumberger website   bloomberg business week retrieved july     schlumberger nv  company information   k retrieved march     schlumberger slb stock price financials and news global  fortune retrieved  september    schlumberger on the forbes global  list forbes retrieved  september    schlumberger water services schlumberger web site retrieved on january    schlumberger carbon services schlumberger web site retrieved on january    listings directory schlumberger limited nyse web site retrieved on september    history of ladd furniture inc fundinguniversecom retrieved    schlumberger research centers schlumberger limited retrieved    history schlumberger slb retrieved january     companies fined  million december     helman christopher august   forbes magazine archived from the original on january     httpwwwflowpathcomwhislbpressreleasehtmunreliable source archived september   at the wayback machine  houston chronicle october     schlumberger buys  venture stake from baker hughes the wall street journal retrieved  march    schlumberger research schlumberger retrieved on january    schlumberger to acquire smith for about  billion update businessweek february   retrieved on february    yahoo finance  schlumberger completes merger with smith international retrieved september     schlumberger to buy geoservices for  billion retrieved from marketwatch  february   schlumberger purchases remaining shares of saxon retrieved  august    nicole hong  march  schlumberger unit to plead guilty to viol